Hello,

So am trying to enroll in summer CS61C (this summer of course) but I can't because am already enrolled in a class that is set to not allow time conflicts with other classes. For context, I am currently enrolled in IntegBi 128 since it satisfies the Natural Sciences requirement. This is offered in session A whereas CS61C is offered in session C so ideally, I would only miss the first few lectures of CS61C which will be web-casted anyway. Does anyone know how to get around this? Is there an application form for course overrides that I can fill? Please help! (Need to knock out these two requirements so I can jump straight to upper divs starting this Fall)
